The paper deals with the topic of differential privacy, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses logics and type systems for privacy-preserving algorithms, which are topics in programming languages and formal methods (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LO). The implementation of the prototype, Fuzzi, involves database systems (cs.DB) and machine learning algorithms (cs.AI).
